<subSubSection pageNumber="806" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="806">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="806">Note:</emphasis>
As has been noted by Barrie &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="806">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 511. 1992), the typification made by Reveal &amp; al. is pre-dated by the competing choice of Sherif &amp; Siddiqi (in El-Gadi, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="806">Fl. Libya</emphasis>
145: 328. 1988), who chose 77.2 (LINN), a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Labill.) Warb" authorityName="Warb" baseAuthorityName="Labill." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Miscanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="806">Miscanthus floridulus</emphasis>
(Labill.) Warb
</taxonomicName>
, ex Schum. &amp; Lander. It appears that a conservation proposal may be necessary but in the meantime, Art. 57.1 applies, and no change in the application of the name should occur.
</paragraph>
